---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '~/lib/siteConfig'
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`About — ${SITE_CONFIG.name}`}
  description={`What ${SITE_CONFIG.name} is and how it fits in the oriz family.`}
>
  <header class="prose-spine page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">finance</a> / about</p>
    <h1>About oriz finance</h1>
  </header>

  <article class="prose-spine prose">
    <p class="lede">
      <strong>{SITE_CONFIG.name}</strong> — {SITE_CONFIG.tagline}.
    </p>

    <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
    <p>
      Most online financial calculators in India are wrappers around a single
      formula glued to a lead-capture form. Finance flips that: the math is
      the product. Each calculator shows you the formula it used, the
      assumptions it made, and the year-by-year breakdown when one exists.
      No sign-up, no "talk to an advisor" popups, no affiliate redirects
      between you and the answer.
    </p>

    <h2>What it covers</h2>
    <p>
      <span class="num">28</span> calculators across four ledgers — Investments,
      Loans &amp; EMI, Banking &amp; savings, Tax &amp; salary. SIP, lumpsum,
      step-up SIP, SWP, FIRE, CAGR/XIRR, goal planner. Home, car, personal,
      and prepayment EMIs with full amortization. FD, RD, PPF, NPS, NSC, SSY,
      compound interest. Take-home pay, HRA exemption, gratuity, leave
      encashment, GST, income tax. Calculators get added when the math is
      unambiguous and the inputs are commonly asked.
    </p>

    <h2>What it is not</h2>
    <p>
      Not investment advice. Not a SEBI-registered advisor. Not a place to
      open an account, take a loan, or buy insurance. Outputs are
      mathematical projections from your inputs, nothing more — see the
      <a href="/legal/disclaimer/">SEBI/IRDAI/RBI disclaimer</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Part of oriz</h2>
    <p>
      Finance is one of <span class="num">11</span> static sites under
      <a href="https://oriz.in">oriz.in</a> — built by Chirag Singhal,
      deployed to Cloudflare's edge, sharing one Firebase sign-in across
      the family. See the <a href="https://oriz.in">oriz hub</a> for the
      full lineup, or the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> if you spot
      a calculation that looks off.
    </p>

    <h2>Type, grid, signature</h2>
    <p>
      The page is a printed graph sheet — an 8px CSS grid lives behind every
      view, fixed to the viewport so scrolling reads as paper sliding under
      a fixed sheet. Headlines are set in <strong>Fraunces</strong> at one
      size only. Body is <strong>Source Sans 3</strong>. Every numeric is
      <strong>JetBrains Mono</strong> with tabular nums + slashed zero. The
      two motifs that belong only to finance — leader-dotted TOC rows and
      the <code>══</code> double-rule totals row — show up everywhere a
      list or a sum is rendered.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
